data.description: It’s not often that a golf course home like this comes on the market.  This property is located on the 16th green of Caloosa Country Club which is the only private golf course in Sun City Center. This is a well maintained, bright and airy Twintree model floor plan featuring 1756 sq. ft. of airconditioned living space, dual master suites, 2 baths, a Florida room, and a 2-car garage. There are no worries about your 4 Point insurance inspection here.  A new A/C was installed and the electrical was updated in 2023.  A new water heater was installed in 2022, a new roof was installed in 2012 and the plumbing was changed to CPVC in 2010.  Other improvements include a water softener, reverse osmosis in the kitchen and a new aluminum pull down ladder for the attic. It is located in Sun City Center, FL and is centrally located giving convenient access to shopping, community amenities and medical facilities.   Entering the house, you are greeted with a large living room/dining room combination that provides you room for multiple furniture arrangements.  The kitchen is centrally located with plenty of lighting and lots of cabinet space.  The large airconditioned laundry room is off the kitchen and has plenty of cabinets for extra storage.  The large primary suite can easily accommodate king sized furniture and has 2 closets, one being a large walk-in. When you have family or guests visiting, the second master suite features a pocket door that closes off the bedroom and the bathroom from the main living space offering everyone convenience and privacy.  The family room has access to the Florida room, one of the rooms with a magnificent view of the golf course, and both of which give you great space for entertaining or just relaxing. Sun City Center is one of Florida’s premier active 55+ adult communities with an abundance of clubs and activities for its residents to enjoy.  Orland’s many attractions are only 90 minutes away.  If cruising and traveling are your thing you are only about 45 minutes from both the airport and the cruise terminal.  If you prefer to stay closer to home the Tampa Bay area offers many great attractions, dining, and some of the best beaches in the world.
